(firstQuint)Circadian Rhythm and Attack-timing in Episodic Cluster Headache Patients in- and Outside of Bout: an Actigraphic Study.

 The aim is to investigate circadian rhythm in episodic cluster headache patients in- and outside of bout.

 This will be done using actigraphy and a short diary for 2 weeks in each period.

 A secondary outcome is to look at attack occurence and physical activity before and during an attack.

